  <h2 class="section-heading" id="step-2" data-jump-label="Step 2: Build in Claude Chat">Step 2: Build Your Skill in Claude Chat</h2>
  <p class="section-description">Open a <strong>new conversation</strong> in claude.ai or the Claude app. Paste the following prompt, filling in your information from Step 1.</p>

  <div class="terminal-window">
    <div class="terminal-header">
      <div class="terminal-dot red"></div>
      <div class="terminal-dot yellow"></div>
      <div class="terminal-dot green"></div>
      <span class="terminal-title">build prompt</span>
    </div>
    <div class="terminal-content">I want to build a personal daily briefing skill for Claude.
Here's my information:

[Paste your completed worksheet from Step 1]

Please build this as a .skill file with:
1. SKILL.md — the briefing instructions Claude follows when I say
   "let's start our day"
2. references/context.md — my consolidated knowledge base

Important requirements:
- Work with MCP connectors: Slack, Gmail, Calendar, Drive, Granola
- If any data source fails, continue with the remaining sources
- Include error handling (especially Granola, which can be flaky)
- Google Docs use google_drive_fetch; Sheets need Chrome browser tools
- Cross-reference signals across systems, don't just list them
- End with "Over to you" and contextual follow-up prompts
- Include day-specific logic (Monday OKR reminders, heavy meeting
  day prep, Friday wrap-up)

Package it as a downloadable .skill file when done.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="cowork-response">
    <h6>What Happens Next</h6>
    <ul>
      <li>Claude asks clarifying questions (e.g., "Which Slack channels are highest priority?")</li>
      <li>Creates the SKILL.md with your customized briefing flow</li>
      <li>Creates references/context.md with your consolidated knowledge base</li>
      <li>Validates the skill format</li>
      <li>Packages and presents a downloadable <code>.skill</code> file</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="key-point">
    <p><strong>This takes one conversation</strong> — usually 10-20 minutes.</p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="section-heading" id="step-3" data-jump-label="Step 3: Install Your Skill">Step 3: Install Your Skill</h2>
  <p class="section-description">Three steps:</p>

  <ol style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: #4b5563; font-size: 0.9375rem;">
    <li style="padding: 0.375rem 0;"><strong>Download</strong> the <code>.skill</code> file Claude created (appears as a downloadable file in the chat)</li>
    <li style="padding: 0.375rem 0;"><strong>Go to</strong> claude.ai &rarr; <strong>Settings &rarr; Skills</strong></li>
    <li style="padding: 0.375rem 0;"><strong>Upload</strong> your <code>.skill</code> file</li>
  </ol>

  <p class="section-description">The skill is now active across all your conversations. No additional setup needed.</p>

  <CalloutBox type="limitation" title="How to Update Your Skill Later">
    Start a new Claude chat, upload your current <code>.skill</code> file (or the individual SKILL.md and context.md), describe what you want to change, and ask Claude to rebuild. Then re-upload the new <code>.skill</code> file to replace the old one.
  </CalloutBox>

  <h2 class="section-heading" id="step-4" data-jump-label="Step 4: Run Your First Briefing">Step 4: Run Your First Briefing</h2>
  <p class="section-description">Open a <strong>new conversation</strong> (not the one you used to build). Type:</p>

  <div class="terminal-window">
    <div class="terminal-header">
      <div class="terminal-dot red"></div>
      <div class="terminal-dot yellow"></div>
      <div class="terminal-dot green"></div>
      <span class="terminal-title">prompt</span>
    </div>
